t_img,q_cdnize,to_webp,s_webp/joythebaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/0S9A1956-683x1024.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 data-start=\"3124\" data-end=\"3158\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://joythebaker.com/2017/09/brunch-cocktail-in-a-can-micheladas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e\u003cstrong data-start=\"3131\" data-end=\"3156\"\u003eMicheladas in the Can\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp data-start=\"3159\" data-end=\"3567\"\u003eWhen it’s so hot that a cold beer suddenly becomes an important hydration strategy. This michelada is mixed \u003cem data-start=\"3320\" data-end=\"3338\"\u003eright in the can\u003c/em\u003e with tomato juice, clam juice (trust the process), lime, and a good hit of Tajín. It’s salty, spicy, and ice cold.  It’s the kind of drink that saves your life just a little bit. Bonus: it’s also the easiest cocktail you’ll make all summer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
